Learn a Programming Language
Python

Visit the Detailed Version
If you already have some DevOps experience,
visit the detailed version with more topics.
You can pick any programming language. The purpose
behind the language is to be able to write automation
scripts to automate repetitive tasks.
Pick any Programming Language
DevOps is all about bringing developers and operations
teams together to improve software delivery. The key focus
areas are automation, infrastructure and monitoring.
What is DevOps?
For further details, have a look at the FAQs below.
Linux
Learn about the file system, package managers, managing
services, checking logs, bash scripting, permissions, pipes
output redirection, common tools for text manipulation
process monitoring, networking tools, CLI editors etc.
Pick Ubuntu if you have a little to no experience.
Networking and Protocols
Learn about DNS, TCP/IP Protocols, SSH, ports, gateways,
routing, ip addressing, and subnetting etc.
This will come in handy with deployments / troubleshooting
Docker
Learn about containerization. Be comfortable writing
Docker files. Learn about troubleshooting. Get familiar with
Alpine Linux. Learn about networking, storage, security.
Learn docker networking, storage, security, performance.
Git
DevOps teams usually practice "git ops," i.e., making
changes to your CI/CD pipeline, infrastructure, or server
provisioning will involve making a pull request against
the appropriate git repository.
Learn about git, create your GitHub profile.
AWS
Pick one of the cloud providers AWS, GCP or Azure.
Start with core services e.g. in AWS VPC, EC2, S3, IAM
and later RDS, Route53, Cloudwatch, ECS, etc.
Create and deploy some dummy application to AWS.
Terraform
Learn what “Infrastructure as Code” means. Learn about
terraform and how to automate infrastructure creation.
If you deployed an application to AWS in previous step
destroy the infrastructure and create it using terraform.
Ansible
Learn what is configuration management. Understand
roles, playbooks, inventory management and automation.
Write some automation scripts e.g. db backups.
GitHub Actions
Learn about the concepts of CI/CD and how to implement
in your projects using some CI/CD tool. There are several
options available in this space, you can pick any one.
Integrate CI/CD into your apps using GitHub Actions.
Nginx
nginx is commonly used for web serving, reverse proxying,
caching, load balancing, media streaming, and more.
Learn the basic config options, TLS setup etc.
Look at the detailed version for what else you don’t know
DevOps Roadmap
At this point, you should have enough knowledge to find a junior to
mid-level (maybe even senior) DevOps position at any company
depending on the depth of your knowledge.
Job Ready
Deepen your pool of knowledge  and keep building projects till you
find a job. Your job will teach you a lot as well.
